SYNOPSIS
========
   int valid_exec(string name, object ob, object obfrom)

DESCRIPTION
===========
   Validate the rebinding of an IP connection by usage of exec(E). Arguments 
   are the name(M) of the _program_ attempting to rebind the connection, the 
   object ob(M) to receive the connection, and the object obfrom(M) giving the
   connection. Note that the program name is not the object_name(E) of the 
   object, and has no leading slash.

   Return 0 to disallow the action, any other value to allow it.

SEE ALSO
========
   exec(E)
